cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DS 

The paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of differential evolution, which is a type of evolutionary algorithm commonly used in optimization problems. The experiments conducted in the paper involve optimization of benchmark functions, parameter tuning of a gene repressilator system, and learning neural networks. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of an evolutionary algorithm and evaluates it on learning neural networks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper evaluates the proposed approach on learning neural networks, which is a subfield of machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new approach to optimization using an evolutionary algorithm, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper evaluates the proposed approach on parameter tuning of a gene repressilator system, which is a system in the field of systems and control. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new approach to optimization using an evolutionary algorithm, which is a type of algorithm commonly studied in the field of data structures and algorithms.
